    <div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even"><p>If you're trying to make your Drupal site as fast as possible, you might consider using a static HTML file for page not found (404) errors.  There are <a href="https://drupal.org/project/static_404">various</a> <a href="https://drupal.org/project/fast_404">other solutions</a> that can help make Drupal faster in these situations while still letting you take advantage of Drupal-level <a href="https://drupal.org/project/redirect">redirects</a> and whatnot, but a static page is always the fastest.</p></div></div></div><div class="field field-name-node-link field-type-ds field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even"><a href="/buzz/simple-static-search-form-for-drupal-sites">Read more</a></div></div></div>
